-- Ukraine’s Luganskteplovoz Cuts 15% Jobs in 2012, Kommersant Says
-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a
-- 2012-06-14T06:40:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-14/ukraine-s-luganskteplovoz-cuts-15-jobs-in-2012-kommersant-says.html
VAT Luganskteplovoz (LTPL) , Ukraine’s
biggest train producer, which is a part of Russia’s ZAO
Transmashholding, seeks to cut 15 percent of jobs this year and
another 10 percent next year,  Kommersant-Ukraine  newspaper
reported, citing plant director Pavel Cesnek.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Kateryna Choursina in Kiev 
